<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8964352-connie"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1522528420i/8964352._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8964352-connie">Connie</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">In my opinion, all of the &quot;disturbing&quot; content was relevant to the story line. There isn&apos;t any gratuitous sex. Drugs and alcohol are certainly not rev<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">In my opinion, all of the "disturbing" content was relevant to the story line. There isn't any gratuitous sex. Drugs and alcohol are certainly not revered (the main character avoids both with good reasons). There are moral dilemmas worked out in a positive way. I found it less disturbing than most news articles I read.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
