<div id="review_2519073493" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2519073493" />
    <a title="Michael" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3680008-michael"><img alt="Michael" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641853236p2/3680008.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2519073493?book_show_action=true">Sep 09, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael" href="/user/show/3680008-michael">Michael</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/36054954-when-never-comes">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3680008-michael?shelf=kindle-prime-electronic">kindle-prime-electronic</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2519073493" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5012369096470351684">This had the potential to be a really amazing book, but the story got really lazy at the end. I liked it in the beginning when Christy was trying to understand what her husband last moments was before he died. It seemed like she was more concerned with the woman he was was with than anything else. I did not think it was a character flaw but it did not make that much sense to me. As far as the story, it was really good in the beginning but then it became to inconsistent.<br/><br/>I tend to disagree with th</span>
  <span id="freeText5012369096470351684" style="display:none">This had the potential to be a really amazing book, but the story got really lazy at the end. I liked it in the beginning when Christy was trying to understand what her husband last moments was before he died. It seemed like she was more concerned with the woman he was was with than anything else. I did not think it was a character flaw but it did not make that much sense to me. As far as the story, it was really good in the beginning but then it became to inconsistent.<br /><br />I tend to disagree with the majority when it come down to overall community rating. Nevertheless, I do not regret that I read it, it was a fascinating on some parts but I did not like how it felt rushed at the end. However, I do plan on reading more books by Davis so that is a good thing. <br /><br />Lastly, I will not recommend the book due to the inconsistency but it was a decent read.</span>
